jobs.description:
E-Work Agenzia per il Lavoro, in collaboration with a prestigious Professional Studio in Reggio Emilia, is looking for a young Chartered Accountant, or equivalent, and a Studio Accountant to join their team.

Job Details:
• Assist clients with tax matters and provide end-user support in tax compliance;
• Calculate taxes for companies and individuals;
• Support the team of professionals in specific tasks;
• Prepare annual and interim financial statements;
• Assist colleagues and studio partners in tax advisory activities;
• Interact with teams dedicated to transaction advisory.

Requirements:
• Master's degree in Business Economics or similar field;
• Knowledge of Tax Law and accounting;
• Ability to work in a goal-oriented team environment;
• Interest in working in a team using English language;
• Proficiency in Excel and PowerPoint for presentations and analysis.

Ideal candidates will have relevant experience in a chartered accountant's studio. They are team players who are eager to... grow professionally.
This position requires a high level of autonomy, suitable for the candidate's expertise. Working closely with the Studio's Ownership, they will handle operational and managerial issues. Professional growth opportunities with stimulating career prospects are offered.

Contract Type: collaboration with VAT number

Location: Reggio Emilia

This job offer is open to all genders in compliance with Legislative Decree 198/2006.
